    {
      "id": "commons-invite",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Invitation",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 980,
        "y": 120
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 250,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Invitation\n\nAdd public repository cards here when they deserve shared visibility. The point is not to hoard links, but to create a living commons of public work that benefits from adjacency.",
        "definitionKey": "markdown",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "markdown",
          "classRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "commons-guidelines",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Guidelines",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 980,
        "y": 450
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Suggested Use\n\n- Add a `github-repo` node for each public repo that belongs here.\n- Use notes on the repo card to explain why it matters.\n- Prefer public-facing repos that are readable, intentional, or worth discovering together.",
        "definitionKey": "markdown",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "markdown",
          "classRef": "/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        }
      }
    },
